60
00:04:04,188 --> 00:04:07,774
A double, I think, Willie.

61
00:04:07,808 --> 00:04:09,743
Something doubly big
on your mind?

62
00:04:09,777 --> 00:04:12,145
[Sighs]

63
00:04:14,648 --> 00:04:16,416
[Sighs]

64
00:04:16,450 --> 00:04:19,953
An old friend passed away.

65
00:04:19,987 --> 00:04:23,173
I'm feeling
a little melancholy.

66
00:04:23,207 --> 00:04:26,042
Good friends
is hard to come by.

67
00:04:26,093 --> 00:04:28,762
All mine are deader than shit.

68
00:04:28,796 --> 00:04:33,016
Gutshot, poison,
pox, bad wives, you name it.

69
00:04:33,050 --> 00:04:34,851
Hmm.

70
00:04:34,885 --> 00:04:38,104
How did yours die?

71
00:04:38,139 --> 00:04:40,440
Greed, I think.

72
00:04:40,474 --> 00:04:44,310
His reach exceeded his grasp.

73
00:04:46,313 --> 00:04:47,447
Hold still, now.

74
00:04:47,481 --> 00:04:48,531
Hmm?

75
00:04:48,566 --> 00:04:49,783
Don't wanna nick you.

76
00:04:49,817 --> 00:04:51,551
What are you doing here?

77
00:04:51,585 --> 00:04:53,705
Mormons is building a spur
line railroad of their own.

78
00:04:53,738 --> 00:04:56,156
You want it to come here
or Laramie?

79
00:04:56,190 --> 00:04:57,407
Here, of course.
Ouch.

80
00:04:57,458 --> 00:04:58,658
Sorry.

81
00:04:58,692 --> 00:04:59,959
My pappy taught me
how to shave.

82
00:04:59,994 --> 00:05:01,494
- I'm a little rusty.
- [Sighs]

83
00:05:01,528 --> 00:05:03,246
The Mormons been poaching
my men.

84
00:05:03,297 --> 00:05:06,666
There's bad blood
between me and them.

85
00:05:06,700 --> 00:05:08,802
Please be careful.

86
00:05:08,836 --> 00:05:11,054
- Damn it.
- You got to hold still.

87
00:05:11,088 --> 00:05:12,756
Now, go like this.

88
00:05:12,807 --> 00:05:15,308
- This?
- Yeah.

89
00:05:15,342 --> 00:05:18,762
Yeah, you hired them to do
a survey for you back in '61.

90
00:05:18,813 --> 00:05:22,849
Thought maybe you could broker
a deal to suit us both.

91
00:05:22,883 --> 00:05:26,069
No.

92
00:05:26,103 --> 00:05:29,405
- No.
- Can't or won't?

93
00:05:29,440 --> 00:05:32,108
I won't sully my relations
with the Mormons

94
00:05:32,159 --> 00:05:34,694
with your foundering.

95
00:05:34,728 --> 00:05:36,079
For a man with a straight
razor to his throat,

96
00:05:36,113 --> 00:05:37,530
I don't imagine
you're gulling me.

97
00:05:37,564 --> 00:05:39,199
[Sighs]

98
00:05:39,233 --> 00:05:43,236
Cut my throat
or leave me be, Bohannon.

99
00:05:46,406 --> 00:05:50,076
You're missing one hell
of an opportunity, Durant.

100
00:05:52,579 --> 00:05:55,548
As did you, sir, just now.

101
00:06:00,521 --> 00:06:01,888
Pretty?

102
00:06:01,922 --> 00:06:04,190
Everywhere I looked,
she was pretty, hmm?

103
00:06:04,225 --> 00:06:06,476
You seen Mr. Ferguson?

104
00:06:06,527 --> 00:06:08,311
Yes, sir, but he ain't taking
no visitors right now.

105
00:06:08,362 --> 00:06:09,612
Appreciate you trying
to protect him

106
00:06:09,647 --> 00:06:11,064
but I need him
to ride out with me.

107
00:06:11,098 --> 00:06:12,065
Ain't him I'm trying
to protect.

108
00:06:12,099 --> 00:06:13,399
It's you.

109
00:06:13,433 --> 00:06:15,368
He up there with a bottle
and a gun.

110
00:06:15,402 --> 00:06:16,653
Ain't drawn a sober breath

111
00:06:16,704 --> 00:06:20,490
since Eva gave away the baby.

112
00:06:20,541 --> 00:06:22,992
He a little dangerous
right now.

113
00:06:23,043 --> 00:06:25,083
A man who's lost everything's
got nothing to lose.

114
00:06:25,112 --> 00:06:28,047
- Can he ride?
- Ride a horse?

115
00:06:28,082 --> 00:06:29,749
'Bout only thing
he can do right now

116
00:06:29,783 --> 00:06:32,218
is roll off that roof
and break his damn fool neck.

117
00:06:32,253 --> 00:06:34,137
Might sober his ass up.

118
00:06:34,171 --> 00:06:35,755
Elam.

119
00:06:35,789 --> 00:06:38,591
Elam Ferguson.

120
00:06:40,794 --> 00:06:42,312
What you want?

121
00:06:42,346 --> 00:06:46,850
You plan on coming down
off there anytime soon?

122
00:06:46,901 --> 00:06:50,270
I ain't decided yet.

123
00:06:50,304 --> 00:06:54,657
You make a decision, son,
or I'll make it for you.

124
00:06:54,692 --> 00:06:58,661
Son of a bitch.
That's a threat?

125
00:06:58,696 --> 00:07:02,198
It's a warning.

126
00:07:02,249 --> 00:07:03,950
Get his ass straight
or you get him outta here.

127
00:07:03,984 --> 00:07:06,586
- I need every man working.
- I ain't his pappy.

128
00:07:06,620 --> 00:07:08,755
And I ain't got time
for his shit.

129
00:07:08,789 --> 00:07:10,506
I aim to be spiking rail
right through Cheyenne

130
00:07:10,541 --> 00:07:12,258
in ten days
or God himself tell me why not.

131
00:07:12,293 --> 00:07:14,344
Do you understand me?

132
00:07:14,378 --> 00:07:16,763
Yes, sir, Mr. Bohannon.

133
00:07:16,797 --> 00:07:18,598
Good.

134
00:07:18,632 --> 00:07:22,886
[Indistinct chatter]

135
00:07:51,031 --> 00:07:53,666
I'm looking
for a Thomas Durant.

136
00:07:53,700 --> 00:07:56,419
What's your business, stranger?

137
00:07:56,470 --> 00:07:59,639
Commonwealth Detective Malone,
Boston, Massachusetts.

138
00:07:59,673 --> 00:08:02,392
Executive office.
Is that good enough for you?

139
00:08:02,426 --> 00:08:05,311
Sure is. He's probably
getting his morning shave.

140
00:08:05,346 --> 00:08:08,097
Is this where Senator Metcalf
was staying?

141
00:08:08,148 --> 00:08:09,732
Only place in town.

142
00:08:09,767 --> 00:08:11,851
I figured it was.

143
00:08:11,885 --> 00:08:13,119
- You know where he went?
- No, sir.

144
00:08:13,153 --> 00:08:17,657
Just disappeared into thin air.

145
00:08:17,691 --> 00:08:20,360
- Got any rooms?
- Oh, I can give you his.

146
00:08:33,474 --> 00:08:36,342
I have no idea
what happened to Metcalf.

147
00:08:36,377 --> 00:08:38,544
And that's the truth.

148
00:08:38,578 --> 00:08:42,632
We burned him

149
00:08:42,683 --> 00:08:44,300
with the cholera victims.

150
00:08:44,351 --> 00:08:46,769
I don't know that.

151
00:08:46,804 --> 00:08:48,271
Well, I'm telling you.

152
00:08:48,305 --> 00:08:49,889
Don't.

153
00:08:49,923 --> 00:08:52,809
I can't tell the truth
if I don't know it.

154
00:08:52,860 --> 00:08:56,362
[Knock at door]

155
00:08:56,397 --> 00:08:59,399
Mr. Durant.

156
00:09:01,268 --> 00:09:03,119
[Sighs]

157
00:09:03,153 --> 00:09:07,240
- Why don't you stay?
- All right.

158
00:09:07,274 --> 00:09:10,493
Special Agent Malone.

159
00:09:10,544 --> 00:09:14,280
Nice, uh, suite you got here.

160
00:09:19,619 --> 00:09:21,721
Why did Senator Metcalf
stay behind

161
00:09:21,755 --> 00:09:25,925
when General Grant, Oaks Ames,
and the board left?

162
00:09:25,959 --> 00:09:29,062
- He didn't stay here.
- Desk clerk said he did.

163
00:09:29,096 --> 00:09:31,314
Well, perhaps for a day or two.

164
00:09:31,348 --> 00:09:33,433
Did he say where he was going?

165
00:09:33,467 --> 00:09:34,600
Oh, he would have no reason

166
00:09:34,634 --> 00:09:37,770
to tell me his travel plans.

167
00:09:39,773 --> 00:09:42,025
His wife says
you are childhood friends.

168
00:09:42,076 --> 00:09:45,028
Perhaps yes.

169
00:09:45,079 --> 00:09:47,280
But we had...
[Laughs]

170
00:09:47,314 --> 00:09:50,316
we had very
different childhoods.

171
00:09:53,921 --> 00:09:56,873
[Tense music]

172
00:09:56,924 --> 00:10:00,259
♪

173
00:10:00,294 --> 00:10:04,797
[Clears throat]

174
00:10:04,831 --> 00:10:06,766
Whiskey tumbler.

175
00:10:06,800 --> 00:10:09,435
It fell against the wall.

176
00:10:33,193 --> 00:10:36,829
When was the last time
you saw the senator?

177
00:10:36,863 --> 00:10:39,465
With, uh, some
of the hotel guests.

178
00:10:39,500 --> 00:10:42,502
I'm sure he can't remember.

179
00:10:44,505 --> 00:10:47,423
Can't say I do remember.

180
00:11:01,388 --> 00:11:03,389
Good day, gentlemen.

181
00:11:08,495 --> 00:11:10,246
[Door closes]

182
00:11:10,280 --> 00:11:13,116
And that's how it's done.

183
00:11:21,175 --> 00:11:23,426
Where are you going?

184
00:11:23,460 --> 00:11:25,211
I'm getting
the hell out of here.

185
00:11:25,245 --> 00:11:28,714
Let's not appear to be fearful.

186
00:11:45,699 --> 00:11:48,568
I'll only be gone a few days.
He gonna be any trouble?

187
00:11:48,602 --> 00:11:49,902
Well, he won't bathe.

188
00:11:49,936 --> 00:11:51,621
And while you were in Cheyenne,

189
00:11:51,655 --> 00:11:55,992
he pulled that knife when
I asked him to sweep the church.

190
00:11:56,043 --> 00:11:57,376
Boy, don't you know better

191
00:11:57,411 --> 00:11:58,711
than to pull a knife
on a church lady?

192
00:11:58,745 --> 00:12:00,830
You're not going to hurt him,
are you?

193
00:12:00,881 --> 00:12:02,999
He ain't mine to whup.

194
00:12:03,050 --> 00:12:05,918
Get your gear, boy.
You're coming with me.

195
00:12:05,952 --> 00:12:07,803
He might've fallen off
a Mormon wagon.

196
00:12:07,838 --> 00:12:09,439
Maybe somebody at the fort
will want him.

197
00:12:09,456 --> 00:12:12,141
Will he be safe
traveling that far?

198
00:12:12,176 --> 00:12:13,509
Safe as me, I reckon.

199
00:12:13,560 --> 00:12:15,728
You get frisky
with that knife again,

200
00:12:15,762 --> 00:12:18,014
I'm gonna leave you
to the Indians.

201
00:12:18,065 --> 00:12:20,683
He doesn't think
you really will.

202
00:12:20,734 --> 00:12:23,736
He don't know me so well.
Come on.

203
00:12:27,107 --> 00:12:29,692
I have reconsidered
your request

204
00:12:29,743 --> 00:12:33,579
to negotiate with the Mormons
on your behalf.

205
00:12:33,614 --> 00:12:35,831
Somebody smoked your tree.

206
00:12:35,866 --> 00:12:37,583
You out on a limb?

207
00:12:37,618 --> 00:12:39,285
Colorful, Mr. Bohannon,
but no.

208
00:12:39,319 --> 00:12:41,537
I assure you
I am acting without duress.

209
00:12:41,588 --> 00:12:43,839
Might be trouble up ahead
where it is I'm going.

210
00:12:43,874 --> 00:12:45,541
Don't need it following me too.

211
00:12:45,592 --> 00:12:47,343
Now, there's one you wanna keep
your knife handy for.

212
00:12:47,377 --> 00:12:52,131
You got me?
All right.

213
00:12:52,165 --> 00:12:53,635
Let's ride.

214
00:13:00,507 --> 00:13:02,508
Come on.

215
00:13:07,169 --> 00:13:09,237
Right there.

216
00:13:09,272 --> 00:13:11,973
See the way the hawk dropped
something on the rise?

217
00:13:12,007 --> 00:13:13,391
Probably snatched up his lunch

218
00:13:13,442 --> 00:13:16,444
afore he realized
it was a rattlesnake.

219
00:13:21,817 --> 00:13:24,202
Why you keep looking back, doc?

220
00:13:24,236 --> 00:13:27,455
We're in Mormon country now.

221
00:13:27,490 --> 00:13:29,157
Thought you said
you was friendly with Mormons.

222
00:13:29,191 --> 00:13:33,244
I've had my dealings
with them, yes.

223
00:13:33,296 --> 00:13:36,298
That don't comfort me none.

224
00:13:39,034 --> 00:13:41,920
Who is that boy?

225
00:13:41,971 --> 00:13:43,638
Just a mute boy.

226
00:13:43,673 --> 00:13:45,593
Probably fell off
one of the Mormon wagon trains.

227
00:13:45,641 --> 00:13:47,058
Happens sometimes.

228
00:13:47,093 --> 00:13:50,929
So you've adopted him
as your pet, hmm?

229
00:13:50,980 --> 00:13:53,431
Thought I'd trade in
my walking bosses for him.

230
00:13:53,482 --> 00:13:56,851
Oh, and what are you planning
to offer the Mormons

231
00:13:56,885 --> 00:13:58,937
in exchange for your men?

232
00:13:58,988 --> 00:14:03,191
Open passage west on the U.P.
for their settlers.

233
00:14:03,225 --> 00:14:06,945
Free rail tickets.
Hmm, you <i>are</i> desperate.

234
00:14:06,996 --> 00:14:08,413
Why the hell else
would I bring you?

235
00:14:08,447 --> 00:14:10,999
[Chuckles]

236
00:14:30,136 --> 00:14:32,687
You the sheriff here?

237
00:14:36,976 --> 00:14:39,144
Chief of railroad police.

238
00:14:41,897 --> 00:14:43,815
What?

239
00:14:43,866 --> 00:14:45,650
Oh, nothing.

240
00:14:45,701 --> 00:14:48,069
Just didn't figure on
the chief of police to be so--

241
00:14:48,103 --> 00:14:49,871
Black.

242
00:14:49,905 --> 00:14:51,573
Drunk.

243
00:14:56,078 --> 00:14:58,012
Ain't a crime out here.

244
00:14:58,047 --> 00:15:00,248
Detective Malone.

245
00:15:00,282 --> 00:15:02,384
Boston Police.

246
00:15:02,418 --> 00:15:04,969
Got a minute?

247
00:15:05,004 --> 00:15:08,056
Just a few questions.

248
00:15:08,090 --> 00:15:12,844
[Breathing shakily]

249
00:15:12,895 --> 00:15:14,646
- We got trouble, Mickey.
- Not me.

250
00:15:14,680 --> 00:15:17,015
Copper's asking questions
about Metcalf,

251
00:15:17,066 --> 00:15:21,352
- and Durant made me look--
- What?

252
00:15:21,404 --> 00:15:23,104
He made me look guilty.

253
00:15:23,138 --> 00:15:25,490
- I warned you about Durant.
- I know.

254
00:15:25,524 --> 00:15:27,575
And you were right.

255
00:15:27,610 --> 00:15:31,579
This copper
is from Boston, Sean.

256
00:15:31,614 --> 00:15:34,332
Mickey, what are we gonna do?

257
00:15:34,366 --> 00:15:36,367
You're gonna get as far away
from me as you can

258
00:15:36,419 --> 00:15:40,205
'cause all you ever do
is bring trouble.

259
00:15:40,256 --> 00:15:42,340
So go, be gone.

260
00:15:42,374 --> 00:15:44,659
I don't know you.

261
00:15:51,934 --> 00:15:55,437
Why don't you do us all
a favor, Sean?

262
00:15:55,471 --> 00:15:57,689
Disappear.

263
00:15:57,723 --> 00:16:00,725
Just poof, thin air.

264
00:16:00,776 --> 00:16:04,012
Don't even leave a stink.

265
00:16:06,782 --> 00:16:08,783
All right.

266
00:16:08,818 --> 00:16:09,939
Fade into these cottonwoods.

267
00:16:09,952 --> 00:16:11,536
You hear any gunfire,

268
00:16:11,570 --> 00:16:15,022
you hightail it back
to the railroad, you hear me?

269
00:16:42,351 --> 00:16:44,435
[In Mandarin accent]
Gentlemen!

270
00:16:44,487 --> 00:16:46,454
Collis Huntington.

271
00:16:46,489 --> 00:16:47,489
If you're here
after your deserted workers,

272
00:16:47,523 --> 00:16:49,023
you're too late.

273
00:16:49,057 --> 00:16:51,242
They and the Mormons
are already in my employ.

274
00:16:51,277 --> 00:16:52,794
Thems is my men.

275
00:16:52,828 --> 00:16:54,996
May I suggest we camp
in yonder meadow

276
00:16:55,030 --> 00:16:57,799
out of rifle shot
of that gloomy place?

277
00:16:57,833 --> 00:16:59,033
Mr. Scoggins.

278
00:16:59,068 --> 00:17:01,202
[Speaking Mandarin]

279
00:17:01,237 --> 00:17:04,672
[Speaking Mandarin]

280
00:17:04,707 --> 00:17:07,008
We'll camp for dinner.

281
00:17:07,042 --> 00:17:10,044
[Rings bell]

282
00:17:26,028 --> 00:17:28,363
I ain't got time
to be lollygagging around here.

283
00:17:28,397 --> 00:17:33,034
This is a fortuitous turn
for both of us.

284
00:17:33,068 --> 00:17:36,103
Who would you rather deal
with, Huntington or the Mormons?

285
00:17:37,823 --> 00:17:39,324
Just behave yourself at dinner,

286
00:17:39,375 --> 00:17:42,377
and let me do the talking.

287
00:17:56,342 --> 00:17:58,726
Mr. Bohannon,
my spies tell me

288
00:17:58,761 --> 00:18:01,312
that your railroad
is faltering.

289
00:18:01,347 --> 00:18:02,647
We had some setbacks--

290
00:18:02,681 --> 00:18:05,350
weather and Indians
and rustlers.

291
00:18:05,401 --> 00:18:07,402
Cholera hit us hard.

292
00:18:07,436 --> 00:18:09,654
Some of my men went over there
just for food and water.

293
00:18:09,688 --> 00:18:12,190
This is Mormon territory,
gentlemen.

294
00:18:12,241 --> 00:18:14,025
They are fastidious
about interlopers,

295
00:18:14,076 --> 00:18:15,877
especially negroes
and the oriental.

296
00:18:15,911 --> 00:18:19,080
My deal with Brigham Young
forbids Chinese labor.

297
00:18:19,114 --> 00:18:20,715
I'm gonna need men
to build through here.

298
00:18:20,749 --> 00:18:22,584
It's a long walk back
for your Chinamen.

299
00:18:22,618 --> 00:18:24,002
Their country
has been decimated.

300
00:18:24,036 --> 00:18:27,288
Human meat hangs in the markets
at Nanjing.

301
00:18:27,322 --> 00:18:31,009
My workers
will settle in California.

302
00:18:31,043 --> 00:18:33,511
By the turn of the century,
I predict Mandarin

303
00:18:33,545 --> 00:18:36,097
will be the state's
second language.

304
00:18:36,131 --> 00:18:40,018
Thank you, Mr. Scoggins.

305
00:18:40,052 --> 00:18:43,054
I, um--
I hired some Mormons

306
00:18:43,105 --> 00:18:45,523
for some of my early surveys,

307
00:18:45,557 --> 00:18:47,025
summer of '61.

308
00:18:47,059 --> 00:18:49,944
Yeah, and it cost me
$1/4 million last week

309
00:18:49,979 --> 00:18:52,230
to regain Brigham Young's
confidence in railroad men.

310
00:18:52,281 --> 00:18:54,482
[Laughs]
I had to pay that and some

311
00:18:54,516 --> 00:18:56,651
to get reliable maps
of this region

312
00:18:56,685 --> 00:19:00,154
to replace the worthless charts
they'd supplied me.

313
00:19:00,188 --> 00:19:03,374
Horseshit.
You chose to cheat 'em.

314
00:19:03,409 --> 00:19:05,159
Regardless, you're through
in the west, Thomas.

315
00:19:05,193 --> 00:19:07,545
You know, I replace him

316
00:19:07,579 --> 00:19:09,764
