388
00:23:15,752 --> 00:23:19,589
- Chinese candy.
- He's already asleep.

389
00:23:19,623 --> 00:23:21,591
Thought you only
spoke Chinaman.

390
00:23:21,625 --> 00:23:25,144
I am Chinese,
born and raised in Peking.

391
00:23:25,179 --> 00:23:27,263
Hmm.

392
00:23:35,439 --> 00:23:39,025
You hung a Mormon boy, I heard.

393
00:23:41,195 --> 00:23:42,411
Pretty sure his father
killed my chief of police

394
00:23:42,446 --> 00:23:44,447
and blamed his son.

395
00:23:44,481 --> 00:23:46,833
That's not
how they're telling it.

396
00:23:46,867 --> 00:23:48,334
Bet not.

397
00:23:48,368 --> 00:23:50,369
Thank you,
Mr. Scoggins.

398
00:23:59,880 --> 00:24:01,881
Brandy.

399
00:24:13,277 --> 00:24:16,028
These Mormons
fought our government

400
00:24:16,063 --> 00:24:18,814
across Missouri and Illinois
into Utah.

401
00:24:18,848 --> 00:24:21,234
Massacres have been attributed
to their militias.

402
00:24:21,285 --> 00:24:24,120
Brigham Young has vowed
to avenge

403
00:24:24,154 --> 00:24:26,572
the blood of his prophets
on anyone who crosses them.

404
00:24:26,623 --> 00:24:28,875
That would include you

405
00:24:28,909 --> 00:24:33,045
if they were to catch you
over there, son.

406
00:24:33,080 --> 00:24:35,915
I need them men.

407
00:24:35,966 --> 00:24:39,886
I'm curious
what you're gonna offer 'em.

408
00:24:39,920 --> 00:24:42,805
Smoking my pipe
to figure that out.

409
00:24:42,839 --> 00:24:44,307
[Clears throat]

410
00:24:44,341 --> 00:24:49,011
What is it you want
out of all this?

411
00:24:49,045 --> 00:24:52,181
I ain't put
too much thought into it.

412
00:24:52,215 --> 00:24:54,650
Let me tell you.

413
00:24:54,685 --> 00:24:56,819
A big house on the beach,

414
00:24:56,853 --> 00:24:58,854
a beautiful wife,

415
00:24:58,888 --> 00:25:01,908
a little boy playing
with a bucket in the sand.

416
00:25:01,942 --> 00:25:04,994
You tell me I'm wrong.

417
00:25:07,063 --> 00:25:09,999
[Sighs]

418
00:25:10,033 --> 00:25:11,334
I guess maybe Durant's right.

419
00:25:11,368 --> 00:25:12,618
Some men are architects,

420
00:25:12,669 --> 00:25:15,621
and others, just builders.

421
00:25:15,672 --> 00:25:17,123
I don't mind it like that.

422
00:25:17,174 --> 00:25:19,592
The offer still stands

423
00:25:19,626 --> 00:25:21,844
to build east with me.

424
00:25:21,878 --> 00:25:23,879
Appreciate it.

425
00:25:25,515 --> 00:25:28,050
I'm heading west
with the U.P.

426
00:25:28,084 --> 00:25:31,304
Good night then.

427
00:25:31,355 --> 00:25:35,141
I'll see your Pacific one day,
Mr. Huntington.

428
00:25:35,192 --> 00:25:37,226
Yes, you will,
Mr. Bohannon,

429
00:25:37,260 --> 00:25:40,029
one way or the other.

430
00:25:43,900 --> 00:25:47,153
Did you really hang a boy?

431
00:25:49,573 --> 00:25:52,107
I knew you could talk
all along.

432
00:25:53,827 --> 00:25:55,077
Did you?

433
00:25:55,111 --> 00:25:57,112
No.

434
00:25:58,548 --> 00:26:00,583
What's your name?

435
00:26:00,617 --> 00:26:02,752
- Ezra.
- Ezra.

436
00:26:06,340 --> 00:26:08,290
Ezra.

437
00:26:09,509 --> 00:26:11,510
[Sighs]

438
00:26:15,965 --> 00:26:18,634
What happened to you?

439
00:26:26,276 --> 00:26:28,444
Yeah.

440
00:26:30,146 --> 00:26:33,282
I understand.

441
00:26:33,316 --> 00:26:36,752
Let's get some rest.

442
00:26:36,787 --> 00:26:39,171
Tomorrow, you're gonna
help me outsmart

443
00:26:39,206 --> 00:26:41,290
two of the smartest men
in the world.

444
00:26:41,324 --> 00:26:42,708
[Grunts]

445
00:26:42,759 --> 00:26:43,876
They don't know
what they don't know

446
00:26:43,927 --> 00:26:45,761
about men like you and me.

447
00:26:45,796 --> 00:26:48,330
And that's a lot.

448
00:26:57,006 --> 00:26:59,308
Mm.

449
00:27:02,446 --> 00:27:05,481
Yeah, I hear ya.

450
00:27:08,285 --> 00:27:10,352
[Sighs]

451
