00:30:03,513 --> 00:30:05,431
Glad you run off
from my railroad now?

496
00:30:05,482 --> 00:30:06,682
Well, reckon it's better
than cholera.

497
00:30:06,716 --> 00:30:08,517
But hell,
they promised us women.

498
00:30:08,551 --> 00:30:10,269
Ain't none.

499
00:30:10,320 --> 00:30:11,820
No whiskey, not even no coffee.
What kind of folks is that?

500
00:30:11,855 --> 00:30:13,355
I can't be seen talking to you,

501
00:30:13,389 --> 00:30:15,190
but I need you back, all right?

502
00:30:15,224 --> 00:30:18,994
Rumor is they'll shoot us
if we try to run away.

503
00:30:19,028 --> 00:30:22,664
I ain't seen it yet,
but just look yonder.

504
00:30:23,733 --> 00:30:24,833
Yeah.

505
00:30:24,868 --> 00:30:27,870
Yeah.

506
00:30:27,904 --> 00:30:29,605
It's about to get
a whole lot worse.

507
00:30:29,639 --> 00:30:32,458
All kinds of shit's
about to get heaped on you, son.

508
00:30:32,509 --> 00:30:34,126
You there!

509
00:30:34,177 --> 00:30:35,844
What's your business?

510
00:30:35,879 --> 00:30:38,514
[Guns cock]

511
00:30:40,082 --> 00:30:44,603
Oh, I found this mute boy
out on the prairie.

512
00:30:44,637 --> 00:30:47,055
Trying to get rid of him.
He one of yours?

513
00:30:47,089 --> 00:30:48,690
- Has he papers?
- No.

514
00:30:48,725 --> 00:30:50,109
Mostly he's got fleas
and rickets.

515
00:30:51,478 --> 00:30:55,147
What's your name, stranger?

516
00:30:55,198 --> 00:30:58,650
This ain't about me.
It's about the boy.

517
00:30:58,701 --> 00:31:00,903
Yeah, well, there's something
about you I don't like.

518
00:31:00,937 --> 00:31:02,788
Hell, there's something
about me

519
00:31:02,822 --> 00:31:06,325
